​= Internal Factions of the ALP

​{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Firebrands are populist radicals led by Eddie Ward. They demand bank nationalization, worker control, and are currently infiltrated by Balmain Trotskyists.">Firebrand</span>!} strength: [+ left_fi_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ left_fi_dissent : dissent +]

​{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Institutionalists follow H.V. Evatt. They are intellectual socialists focused on constitutional reform, the United Nations, and legalistic paths to socialization.">Institutionalist</span>!} strength: [+ left_in_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ left_in_dissent : dissent +]

​{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Center represents the Chifley-Curtin legacy. They balance the party's warring wings while managing the 'Stalemate' war and the welfare state.">Centrist</span>!} strength: [+ center_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ center_dissent : dissent +]

​{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="Right Labor is the domain of the AWU machine. They prioritize industrial peace, nativist policies, and the exclusion of foreign 'Red' or 'Vatican' influence.">Right Labor</span>!} strength: [+ right_union_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ right_union_dissent : dissent +]

​{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Industrial Groups are militant Catholic anti-communists. They operate as a 'party within a party' to purge the Left and promote clerical social teaching.">Industrial Groups</span>!} strength: [+ industrial_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ industrial_dissent : dissent +]

​{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="Social Democrats are the pragmatic modernizers. They seek a mixed economy, alliance with the LDP middle-class, and American-style industrialization.">Pragmatist</span>!} strength: [+ right_socdem_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ right_socdem_dissent : dissent +]

